    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>As a compliance officer,<br/>
I want the Compliance Monitor to evaluate incoming payment events for transaction limit breaches and send detailed email alerts when a breach is detected,<br/>
So that the compliance team is notified immediately with all relevant transaction details and can take appropriate action.</p>

<p>This story builds on Story 1.1's skeleton processor to implement the full processing logic: defense-in-depth status filtering, rejection reason evaluation, email content generation via IEmailContentService, email delivery, configuration of the alert recipient, and structured logging for AlertSent, AlertSkipped, and AlertFailed scenarios.</p>

<h3><a name="AcceptanceCriteria"></a>Acceptance Criteria</h3>

<p><b>Business Criteria (Non-Technical):</b></p>

<p><b>Given</b> a payment event arrives with status "Declined" and rejection reason "TransactionLimitExceeded"<br/>
<b>When</b> the Compliance Monitor processes the event<br/>
<b>Then</b> an email alert is sent to the Compliance inbox containing merchant name, merchant ID, configured limit, attempted amount, timestamp, and percentage above limit<br/>
<b>And</b> no impact to transaction processing performance</p>

<p><b>Given</b> a payment event arrives with status "Approved"<br/>
<b>When</b> the Compliance Monitor processes the event<br/>
<b>Then</b> no email is sent and no error is raised</p>

<p><b>AC-1: Status Filtering (Defense-in-Depth)</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with status not equal to "Declined"</li>
	<li><b>When</b> processed by TransactionLimitExceededProcessor</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> EventGridResult.Acknowledge is returned</li>
	<li><b>And</b> AlertSkipped is logged at Debug level with skipReason: "StatusNotDeclined"</li>
	<li><b>And</b> no email is sent</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-2: Limit Breach Rule Match — Email Sent</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with status: "Declined", rejectionReason: "TransactionLimitExceeded", and configuredTransactionLimit is not null</li>
	<li><b>When</b> processed by TransactionLimitExceededProcessor</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> email content is generated via IEmailContentService.GenerateTransactionLimitExceededContent() and sent via IEmailService</li>
	<li><b>And</b> AlertSent is logged at Information level with merchantId, rejectionReason, attemptedAmount, configuredLimit</li>
	<li><b>And</b> EventGridResult.Acknowledge is returned</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-3: Non-Matching Rejection Reason — Skipped</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with status: "Declined" but rejectionReason is NOT "TransactionLimitExceeded"</li>
	<li><b>When</b> processed</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> AlertSkipped is logged at Information level with skipReason: "NonMatchingRejectionReason"</li>
	<li><b>And</b> no email is sent, EventGridResult.Acknowledge returned</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-4: Missing Configured Limit — Skipped</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> a Payment.Debit.Submitted event with status: "Declined", rejectionReason: "TransactionLimitExceeded", but configuredTransactionLimit is null</li>
	<li><b>When</b> processed</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> AlertSkipped is logged at Information level with skipReason: "NoConfiguredLimit"</li>
	<li><b>And</b> no email is sent, EventGridResult.Acknowledge returned</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-5: Email Content Fields</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> a limit breach event is processed successfully</li>
	<li><b>When</b> IEmailContentService.GenerateTransactionLimitExceededContent() is called</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> the email content includes: merchant name, merchant ID (subMerchantAccountId), configured limit, attempted amount, timestamp, and percentage above limit</li>
	<li><b>And</b> percentage above limit is calculated as ((amount - configuredLimit) / configuredLimit) * 100</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-6: Email Send Failure — AlertFailed, NOT Reject</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> a valid limit breach event is processed</li>
	<li><b>When</b> email send throws an exception</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> AlertFailed is logged at Warning level with merchantId, rejectionReason, attemptedAmount, errorMessage</li>
	<li><b>And</b> EventGridResult.Acknowledge is returned (NOT Reject)</li>
	<li><b>And</b> no exception propagates to the caller</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-7: Email Recipient Configuration</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> the Compliance Monitor application is configured</li>
	<li><b>When</b> the processor sends an alert email</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> the recipient is sourced from ComplianceSettings.TransactionLimitAlertRecipient</li>
	<li><b>And</b> the config value is in appsettings.json under the compliance section</li>
</ul>


<p><b>AC-8: Scoped Logging</b></p>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li><b>Given</b> any event is processed</li>
	<li><b>When</b> the processor logs any event (AlertSent, AlertSkipped, AlertFailed)</li>
	<li><b>Then</b> logs include scoped context: Activity = "Process Transaction Limit Alert", MerchantId (subMerchantAccountId), PaymentId</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="TechnicalRequirements"></a>Technical Requirements</h3>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Modify TransactionLimitExceededProcessor.cs to implement full processing logic (replace skeleton)</li>
	<li>Add GenerateTransactionLimitExceededContent method to IEmailContentService</li>
	<li>Implement in EmailContentService using existing blob template loading pattern with key "transaction-limit-exceeded"</li>
	<li>Calculate percentage: ((attemptedAmount - configuredLimit) / configuredLimit) * 100</li>
	<li>Add TransactionLimitAlertRecipient string property to ComplianceSettings</li>
	<li>Add TransactionLimitAlertRecipient to appsettings.json compliance section</li>
	<li>Create placeholder transaction-limit-exceeded.html email template</li>
	<li>Expand TransactionLimitExceededProcessorTests.cs with tests for all AC scenarios</li>
</ul>


<h3><a name="RequirementsFulfilled"></a>Requirements Fulfilled</h3>
<p>FR3, FR4, FR5, FR6, FR7, FR8, FR9, FR10, NFR1, NFR2, NFR3</p>

<h3><a name="Relations"></a>Relations</h3>
<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Blocked by: Story 1.1 (
